#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="an10.75"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an10.75:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 10 "
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 10 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an10.75:0.2"
msgid "8. Ākaṅkhavagga "
msgstr "8. If You Want "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "an10.75:0.3"
msgid "75. Migasālāsutta "
msgstr "75. With Migasālā "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "an10.75:1.1"
msgid "Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme. "
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery. "

msgctxt "an10.75:1.2"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā ānando pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya yena migasālāya upāsikāya nivesanaṃ tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā paññatte āsane nisīdi. "
msgstr "Then Venerable Ānanda robed up in the morning and, taking his bowl and robe, went to the home of the laywoman Migasālā, where he sat on the seat spread out. "

msgctxt "an10.75:1.3"
msgid "Atha kho migasālā upāsikā yenāyasmā ānando tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinnā kho migasālā upāsikā āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "Then the laywoman Migasālā went up to Ānanda, bowed, sat down to one side, and said to him: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli5.138, sc2
msgctxt "an10.75:2.1"
msgid "“Kathaṃ kathaṃ nāmāyaṃ, bhante ānanda, bhagavatā dhammo desito aññeyyo, yatra hi nāma brahmacārī ca abrahmacārī ca ubho samasamagatikā bhavissanti abhisamparāyaṃ. "
msgstr "“Sir, Ānanda, how on earth are we supposed to understand the teaching taught by the Buddha, when the chaste and the unchaste are both reborn in exactly the same place in the next life? "

#. VAR: ārācārī → anācārī (mr)
msgctxt "an10.75:2.2"
msgid "Pitā me, bhante, purāṇo brahmacārī hoti ārācārī virato methunā gāmadhammā. "
msgstr "My father Purāṇa was celibate, set apart, avoiding the common practice of sex. "

msgctxt "an10.75:2.3"
msgid "So kālaṅkato bhagavatā byākato: ‘sakadāgāmī satto tusitaṃ kāyaṃ upapanno’ti. "
msgstr "When he passed away the Buddha declared that he was a once-returner, who was reborn in the company of the Joyful Gods. "

# NOTE: See BB for variants.
msgctxt "an10.75:2.4"
msgid "Pitāmaho me, bhante, isidatto abrahmacārī ahosi sadārasantuṭṭho. "
msgstr "But my uncle Isidatta was not celibate; he lived content with his wife. "

msgctxt "an10.75:2.5"
msgid "Sopi kālaṅkato bhagavatā byākato: ‘sakadāgāmī satto tusitaṃ kāyaṃ upapanno’ti. "
msgstr "When he passed away the Buddha declared that he was also a once-returner, who was reborn in the company of the Joyful Gods. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "an10.75:3.1"
msgid "Kathaṃ kathaṃ nāmāyaṃ, bhante ānanda, bhagavatā dhammo desito aññeyyo, yatra hi nāma brahmacārī ca abrahmacārī ca ubho samasamagatikā bhavissanti abhisamparāyan”ti? "
msgstr "How on earth are we supposed to understand the teaching taught by the Buddha, when the chaste and the unchaste are both reborn in exactly the same place in the next life?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an10.75:3.2"
msgid "“Evaṃ kho panetaṃ, bhagini, bhagavatā byākatan”ti. "
msgstr "“You’re right, sister, but that’s how the Buddha declared it.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "an10.75:4.1"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā ānando migasālāya upāsikāya nivesane piṇḍapātaṃ gahetvā uṭṭhāyāsanā pakkāmi. "
msgstr "Then Ānanda, after receiving almsfood at Migasālā’s house, rose from his seat and left. "

msgctxt "an10.75:4.2"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā ānando pacchābhattaṃ piṇḍapātapaṭikkanto yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho āyasmā ānando bhagavantaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "Then after the meal, on his return from alms-round, Ānanda went to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side, and told him what had happened. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "an10.75:5.1"
msgid "“Idhāhaṃ, bhante, pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya yena migasālāya upāsikāya nivesanaṃ tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā paññatte āsane nisīdiṃ. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an10.75:5.2"
msgid "Atha kho, bhante, migasālā upāsikā yenāhaṃ tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā maṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinnā kho, bhante, migasālā upāsikā maṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli5.139, sc6
msgctxt "an10.75:6.1"
msgid "‘Kathaṃ kathaṃ nāmāyaṃ, bhante ānanda, bhagavatā dhammo desito aññeyyo, yatra hi nāma brahmacārī ca abrahmacārī ca ubho samasamagatikā bhavissanti abhisamparāyaṃ. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an10.75:6.2"
msgid "Pitā me, bhante, purāṇo brahmacārī ahosi ārācārī virato methunā gāmadhammā. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an10.75:6.3"
msgid "So kālaṅkato bhagavatā byākato sakadāgāmī satto tusitaṃ kāyaṃ upapannoti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an10.75:6.4"
msgid "Pitāmaho me, bhante, isidatto abrahmacārī ahosi sadārasantuṭṭho. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an10.75:6.5"
msgid "Sopi kālaṅkato bhagavatā byākato—sakadāgāmī satto tusitaṃ kāyaṃ upapannoti. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc7
msgctxt "an10.75:7.1"
msgid "Kathaṃ kathaṃ nāmāyaṃ, bhante ānanda, bhagavatā dhammo desito aññeyyo, yatra hi nāma brahmacārī ca abrahmacārī ca ubho samasamagatikā bhavissanti abhisamparāyan’ti? "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an10.75:7.2"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, ahaṃ, bhante, migasālaṃ upāsikaṃ etadavocaṃ: "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an10.75:7.3"
msgid "‘evaṃ kho panetaṃ, bhagini, bhagavatā byākatan’”ti. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc8
#. VAR: ammakā ammakapaññā → ambakā ambakapaññā (bj) | andhakā andhakapaññā (s1-3) | ambhakā ambhakapaññā (pts1)
msgctxt "an10.75:8.1"
msgid "“Kā cānanda, migasālā upāsikā bālā abyattā ammakā ammakapaññā, ke ca purisapuggalaparopariye ñāṇe? "
msgstr "“Ānanda, who is this laywoman Migasālā, a foolish incompetent matron, with a matron’s wit? And who is it that knows how to assess individuals? "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc9
msgctxt "an10.75:9.1"
msgid "Dasayime, ānanda, puggalā santo saṃvijjamānā lokasmiṃ. "
msgstr "These ten people are found in the world. "

msgctxt "an10.75:9.2"
msgid "Katame dasa? "
msgstr "What ten? "

msgctxt "an10.75:9.3"
msgid "Idhānanda, ekacco puggalo dussīlo hoti. "
msgstr "Take a certain person who is unethical. "

msgctxt "an10.75:9.4"
msgid "Tañca cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ yathābhūtaṃ nappajānāti, yatthassa taṃ dussilyaṃ aparisesaṃ nirujjhati. "
msgstr "And they don’t truly understand the freedom of heart and freedom by wisdom where that unethical conduct ceases without anything left over. "

msgctxt "an10.75:9.5"
msgid "Tassa savanenapi akataṃ hoti, bāhusaccenapi akataṃ hoti, diṭṭhiyāpi appaṭividdhaṃ hoti, sāmāyikampi vimuttiṃ na labhati. "
msgstr "And they’ve not listened or learned or comprehended theoretically or found even temporary freedom. "

msgctxt "an10.75:9.6"
msgid "So kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā hānāya pareti, no visesāya; "
msgstr "When their body breaks up, after death, they’re headed for a lower place, not a higher. "

msgctxt "an10.75:9.7"
msgid "hānagāmīyeva hoti, no visesagāmī. (1) "
msgstr "They’re going to a lower place, not a higher. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli5.140, sc10
msgctxt "an10.75:10.1"
msgid "Idha panānanda, ekacco puggalo dussīlo hoti. "
msgstr "Take a certain person who is unethical. "

msgctxt "an10.75:10.2"
msgid "Tañca cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti yatthassa taṃ dussilyaṃ aparisesaṃ nirujjhati. "
msgstr "But they truly understand the freedom of heart and freedom by wisdom where that unethical conduct ceases without anything left over. "

