msgstr "They’re going to a lower place, not a higher. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli5.143, sc23
msgctxt "an10.75:23.1"
msgid "Idha panānanda, ekacco puggalo uddhato hoti. "
msgstr "Take a certain person who is restless. "

msgctxt "an10.75:23.2"
msgid "Tañca cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti yatthassa taṃ uddhaccaṃ aparisesaṃ nirujjhati. "
msgstr "But they truly understand the freedom of heart and freedom by wisdom where that restlessness ceases without anything left over. "

msgctxt "an10.75:23.3"
msgid "Tassa savanenapi kataṃ hoti, bāhusaccenapi kataṃ hoti, diṭṭhiyāpi paṭividdhaṃ hoti, sāmāyikampi vimuttiṃ labhati. "
msgstr "And they’ve listened and learned and comprehended theoretically and found at least temporary freedom. "

msgctxt "an10.75:23.4"
msgid "So kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā visesāya pareti, no hānāya; "
msgstr "When their body breaks up, after death, they’re headed for a higher place, not a lower. "

msgctxt "an10.75:23.5"
msgid "visesagāmīyeva hoti, no hānagāmī. (10) "
msgstr "They’re going to a higher place, not a lower. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc24
msgctxt "an10.75:24.1"
msgid "Tatrānanda, pamāṇikā pamiṇanti: "
msgstr "Judgmental people compare them, saying: "

msgctxt "an10.75:24.2"
msgid "‘imassapi teva dhammā, aparassapi teva dhammā. Kasmā nesaṃ eko hīno eko paṇīto’ti? "
msgstr "‘This one has just the same qualities as the other, so why is one worse and one better?’ "

msgctxt "an10.75:24.3"
msgid "Tañhi tesaṃ, ānanda, hoti dīgharattaṃ ahitāya dukkhāya. "
msgstr "This will be for their lasting harm and suffering. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc25
msgctxt "an10.75:25.1"
msgid "Tatrānanda, yvāyaṃ puggalo uddhato hoti tañca cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti yatthassa taṃ uddhaccaṃ aparisesaṃ nirujjhati, "
msgstr "In this case the person who is restless, but truly understands the freedom of heart … "

msgctxt "an10.75:25.2"
msgid "tassa savanenapi kataṃ hoti, bāhusaccenapi kataṃ hoti, diṭṭhiyāpi paṭividdhaṃ hoti, sāmāyikampi vimuttiṃ labhati. "
msgstr "and has listened and learned and comprehended theoretically and found at least temporary freedom "

msgctxt "an10.75:25.3"
msgid "Ayaṃ, ānanda, puggalo amunā purimena puggalena abhikkantataro ca paṇītataro ca. "
msgstr "is better and finer than the other person. "

msgctxt "an10.75:25.4"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu? "
msgstr "Why is that? "

msgctxt "an10.75:25.5"
msgid "Imaṃ hānanda, puggalaṃ dhammasoto nibbahati. "
msgstr "Because the stream of the teaching carries them along. "

msgctxt "an10.75:25.6"
msgid "Tadantaraṃ ko jāneyya aññatra tathāgatena. "
msgstr "But who knows the difference between them except a Realized One? "

msgctxt "an10.75:25.7"
msgid "Tasmātihānanda, mā puggalesu pamāṇikā ahuvattha; "
msgstr "So, Ānanda, don’t be judgmental about people. "

msgctxt "an10.75:25.8"
msgid "mā puggalesu pamāṇaṃ gaṇhittha. "
msgstr "Don’t pass judgment on people. "

msgctxt "an10.75:25.9"
msgid "Khaññati hānanda, puggalesu pamāṇaṃ gaṇhanto. "
msgstr "Those who pass judgment on people harm themselves. "

msgctxt "an10.75:25.10"
msgid "Ahaṃ vā, ānanda, puggalesu pamāṇaṃ gaṇheyyaṃ yo vā panassa mādiso. "
msgstr "I, or someone like me, may pass judgment on people. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc26
msgctxt "an10.75:26.1"
msgid "Kā cānanda, migasālā upāsikā bālā abyattā ammakā ammakapaññā, ke ca purisapuggalaparopariye ñāṇe. "
msgstr "Who is this laywoman Migasālā, a foolish incompetent matron, with a matron’s wit? And who is it that knows how to assess individuals? "

msgctxt "an10.75:26.2"
msgid "Ime kho, ānanda, dasa puggalā santo saṃvijjamānā lokasmiṃ. "
msgstr "These ten people are found in the world. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli5.144, sc27
msgctxt "an10.75:27.1"
msgid "Yathārūpena, ānanda, sīlena purāṇo samannāgato ahosi tathārūpena sīlena isidatto samannāgato abhavissa, nayidha purāṇo isidattassa gatimpi aññassa. "
msgstr "If Isidatta had achieved Purāṇa’s level of ethical conduct, Purāṇa could not have even known Isidatta’s destination. "

msgctxt "an10.75:27.2"
msgid "Yathārūpāya cānanda, paññāya isidatto samannāgato ahosi tathārūpāya paññāya purāṇo samannāgato abhavissa, nayidha isidatto purāṇassa gatimpi aññassa. "
msgstr "And if Purāṇa had achieved Isidatta’s level of wisdom, Isidatta could not have even known Purāṇa’s destination. "

msgctxt "an10.75:27.3"
msgid "Iti kho, ānanda, ime puggalā ubho ekaṅgahīnā”ti. "
msgstr "So both individuals were lacking in one respect.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an10.75:27.4"
msgid "Pañcamaṃ. "
msgstr ""

